Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deletePinBlkg(25.10)                                      deletePinBlkg(25.10)

Name
       deletePinBlkg - Deletes a pin blockage or all pin blockages

Syntax
       deletePinBlkg

       [-help]

       {-name <pinBlkgName> | -all}

       Deletes a pin blockage or all pin blockages.

Parameters
       -all   Specifies that all pin blockages will be deleted.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deletePinBlkg parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deletePinBlkg

       -name <pinBlkgName>
              Specifies the name of the pin blockage. You  can  specify  wild-
              cards (?*) with this parameter.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command deletes the pin blockage PtnPinBlkg1:

       deletePinBlkg -name PtnPinBlkg1

